%N A143821 Decimal expansion of the constant 1/2! + 1/5! + 1/8! + ... = 0.50835 81599 84216 ... .
%C A143821 Define a sequence of real numbers R(n) by R(n) := Sum_{k >= 0} (3*k)^n/(3*k)! for n = 0,1,2... . This constant is R(1); the decimal expansions of R(0) = 1 + 1/3!+ 1/6! + 1/9! + ... and R(2) - R(1) = 1/1! + 1/4! + 1/7! + ... may be found in A143819 and A143820. It is easy to verify that the sequence R(n) satisfies the recurrence relation u(n+3) = 3*u(n+2) - 2*u(n+1) + Sum_{i = 0..n} binomial(n,i) *3^(n-i)*u(i). Hence R(n) is an integral linear combination of R(0), R(1) and R(2) and so also an integral linear combination of R(0), R(1) and R(2) - R(1). Some examples are given below.
%F A143821 Constant = (exp(1) + w*exp(w) + w^2*exp(w^2))/3, where w = exp(2*Pi*i/3). A143819 + A143820 + A143821 = exp(1).
%F A143821 Continued faction: 1/(2 - 2/(61 - 60/(337 - 336/(991 - ... - P(n-1)/((P(n) + 1) - ... ))))), where P(n) = (3*n)*(3*n + 1)*(3*n + 2) for n >= 1. Cf. A346441. - _Peter Bala_, Feb 22 2024
